{"id":"1604.08729","submitter":"Shahram Zarei","authors":"Shahram Zarei, Wolfgang Gerstacker, and Robert Schober","title":"Low-Complexity Hybrid Linear/Tomlinson-Harashima Precoding for Downlink\n  Large-Scale MU-MIMO Systems","comments":"This paper has been submitted for presentation at IEEE Global\n  Communications Conference (Globecom) 2016","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.IT math.IT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper, we propose a novel low-complexity hybrid\nlinear/Tomlinson-Harashima precoder (H-L-THP) for downlink large-scale\nmultiuser multiple-input multiple-output (MU-MIMO) systems. The proposed\nprecoder comprises an inner linear precoder which utilizes only the second\norder statistics of the channel state information (CSI) and outer THPs which\nuse the instantaneous overall CSI of the cascade of the actual channel and the\ninner precoder. The user terminals are divided into groups, where for each\ngroup a THP successively mitigates the intra-group interference, whereas the\ninter-group interference is canceled by the inner linear precoder. Our\nsimulation results show that the bit error rate (BER) of the proposed H-L-THP\nprecoder is close to that of the conventional THP precoder, and is\nsubstantially lower than the BER of the commonly used regularized zero-forcing\n(RZF) precoder. Moreover, we derive exact expressions for the computational\ncomplexity of the proposed H-L-THP precoder in terms of the required numbers of\nfloating-point operations. These results reveal that the proposed H-L-THP\nprecoder has a much lower computational complexity than the conventional THP\nand RZF precoders, and is thus an excellent candidate for practical\nimplementations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 29 Apr 2016 08:20:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-02"}
